    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 lbs mutton, cut into pieces</li>
            <li>1 cup yogurt</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>2 teaspoons red chili powder</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon coriander powder</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon garam masala</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>4 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>2 large onions, finely sliced</li>
            <li>3 tomatoes, pureed</li>
            <li>Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
            <li>Ginger slices for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>nonveg</li>
            <li>indian</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Marinate mutton pieces with yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, turmeric powder, red chili powder, coriander powder, garam masala, and salt. Let it marinate for at least 2 hours or overnight in the refrigerator.</li>
            <li>In a large pan, heat vegetable oil and saut√© the sliced onions until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add the marinated mutton and cook until the meat is browned.</li>
            <li>Pour in the pureed tomatoes and cook until the oil separates from the masala.</li>
            <li>Add water as needed, cover, and simmer until the mutton is tender.</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh coriander leaves and ginger slices.</li>
            <li>Serve hot with rice or naan.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious Mutton Rogan!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
